    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Jan. 3 news article ''A Touch of Spring Knocks the Chill Off New York'' trivializes the tragedy of global warming.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Jan. 3 news article ''A Touch of Spring Knocks the Chill Off New York'' trivializes the tragedy of global warming.</p>
        <p>The freedom to take your shirt off in January is not everyone's idea of heaven. Quite the contrary. Many of us feel trapped in a world gone crazy that we never asked for. Who speaks for us?</p>
        <p>MICHAEL DE NOLA  New York, Jan. 3, 2000</p>
      </block>
